### EK validators 21/38 → 24/38 — Wave 8 (2026-05-04)

**Three new validators bringing live coverage from 21 to 24 of 38 manifest rules.**

**Commit (pending).** New rules implemented:

1. **`sink_must_be_in_BD1`** — inverse-direction spatial check of `cooktop_and_sink_require_countertop_cutout`. Each primary CT with active `cutoff_mode` (∈ {"2","3"}) must have at least one `:sink_base` or `:cooktop_base` whose XY-center is inside its bbox. Catches the orphan-cutout anti-pattern: someone toggled `cutoff_mode` on a CT but forgot to drop the host cabinet underneath. Verified on Villu: 2 CTs with active cutout, both have host (BD1 under N-arm CT, BD3 under E-arm CT). File-naming gotcha (see below) — file is `sink_must_be_in_bd1.rb` (lowercase) even though rule_id keeps uppercase `BD1`.

2. **`over_fridge_mezzanine_required`** — for each fridge instance (def-name regex covering EN brand+kind variants and RU «холодильник»), find a `:upper_cabinet` with X-overlap ≥200mm AND Y-overlap (or Y-gap ≤100mm) AND bottom Z within ±50mm of fridge_top. Skips fridges inside `:fridge_pencil` (integrated antresol) and ceiling-flush fridges (top Z ≥2350mm). Verified on Villu: Samsung Hub Side by Side at top Z=1780mm with TB2#1 at bottom Z=1830mm, X-overlap 661mm, Y-overlap full = passes. **First-pass v1 missed the Y-axis check** — TB1#1 on the E-arm (Y=-1751..-1405) falsely matched a hypothetical fridge at (Y=-3313..-2402) because X-overlap alone wasn't sufficient. Fixed in same session by adding Y_PROXIMITY_MM=100mm constraint. Mezzanine SIZING correctness deferred to v2 (needs scene-meta ceiling).

3. **`pencil_cladding_required`** — each `:oven_pencil`/`:fridge_pencil` instance must have ≥1 PANEL-FACADE ComponentInstance within 200mm 3D AABB-gap of pencil bbox. Strict regex `/\APANEL[_\-]FACADE(?:[_#\-\s]|\z)/i` matches `PANEL_FACADE`/`PANEL-FACADE` but NOT `PANEL_F` (internal pencil panel) or `PANEL_G` (back panel). Verified on Villu: PD1_6 has PANEL-FACADE#3 (touching at Y=-1770) and PANEL-FACADE#12 (touching at Y=-2370), both within 0mm gap = passes. v1 catches the gross "no cladding at all near pencil" anti-pattern; does NOT discriminate room-facing vs wall-facing visible side (needs scene-meta — deferred to v2).

**Auto-discovery filename gotcha (new lesson):** `EkStandards.load_validators` uses `File.basename(path, '.rb').split('_').map(&:capitalize).join` to derive the module name from the file name. Ruby `String#capitalize` lowercases non-first chars: `"BD1".capitalize == "Bd1"`. So a file named `sink_must_be_in_BD1.rb` looks for `EkValidators::SinkMustBeInBd1`, NOT `SinkMustBeInBD1`. If the module is defined with the uppercase variant, `const_get` raises `NameError`, the file is silently dropped from `validators[]`, and the audit summary count is off by one. Fix: lowercase file name AND module name (`sink_must_be_in_bd1.rb` / `SinkMustBeInBd1`). The `RULE_ID` constant inside the file is read separately via regex grep by the orphan check — it can keep the uppercase form to match the manifest entry. This same gotcha applies to any future rule with numeric/uppercase suffix tokens (BD2, TG1, CT_*, etc.) and is now documented in `memory/project_ek_validators.md` Wave 8 design notes.

**Spatial-proximity rule (carry-forward to future validators):** For "above/adjacent" geometric rules, ALWAYS require overlap in BOTH horizontal axes (X AND Y), not just the row-axis. The first-pass `over_fridge_mezzanine_required` checked only X-overlap + Z-proximity and false-positive matched an upper on a different arm of the L-shape because the perpendicular row had the same X range. Fixed by adding Y-overlap requirement. This is now noted as a design rule in the validator infrastructure memory.

**Live audit Villu after Wave 8:** 24/24 validators ok=true, 0 violations, 0 orphans. All three new validators positive-tested on Villu and negative-tested via snapshot mutation (`Marshal.load(Marshal.dump(snap))` + field mutation) — including the pencil-skip path for fridges inside `:fridge_pencil` and the ceiling-flush skip path.

