### EK validators 17/38 → 18/38 — ct_world_bbox_matches_ad_dims (2026-05-04)

**Commit `f1077ed`.** Library `TT_STRAIGHT` def carries a `boundingbox#N` sub-instance with 4 outline edges hardcoded at native length (~2000mm). When AD overrides `l8_axe_203_lenx_fix` to a shorter value, the boundingbox edges DO NOT shrink — DC redraw doesn't regenerate them. Result: `inst.bounds.height` reports 2000mm while AD says 1751mm. BOM/cutlist/report scripts reading `inst.bounds` ship FALSE length facts, contradicting the truth in AD.

Validator fires when world bbox horizontal dimensions don't match the AD pair `{length_mm, depth_mm}` within ±5mm.

**Fix at placement time** (now codified in vault `countertop-eurocut.md` recipe): after `dc.set_attribute` + `dc.redraw`, find and erase the `boundingbox#N` sub-instance from the CT def. `axe_position` carries the visible content; the boundingbox is a vestigial outline marker. Verified live on Villu rebuild — both rebuilt CTs match AD-derived dims after delete (N-arm 2749×778, E-arm 600×1751).

