### EK validator coverage 12/38 → 13/38 + ROLE_REGEX fix (2026-05-04 Wave 5)

**Commit `457de0c`.** Mixed wave: 1 new validator + load-bearing fix that exposed two Wave 4 false-passes.

**ROLE_REGEX boundary fix (load-bearing).** Old `\b` doesn't match between word chars: `BD1` ends with `1` (word) and `_` is also `\w`, so no `\b` boundary fires → `^BD1\b` silently misses `BD1_5` / `PD1_6` / etc. New boundary class `(?:[_#\-\s]|\z)` covers underscore, hash, dash, whitespace, end-of-string. After fix: PD1_6#1 correctly classified as `:oven_pencil`, BD2#1/2 as new `:base_cabinet` role.

**False-passes exposed by ROLE_REGEX fix:**

1. **wall_adjacency** — once PD1_6 entered LOWER_ROLES pool, its bbox X_max=3369 (cladding overhang) pulled e_wall_x past actual carcass wall (3339) and false-flagged BD3 (which IS flush at 3339). Fix: pencils removed from both LOWER_ROLES and wall-derivation pool. Pencil cladding (PANEL-FACADE wraps the column 19-30mm past carcass) is by-design and governed by `pencil_cladding_required` separately.

2. **pencil_appliances_required_when_host v2** — old regex literal `oven` (case-insensitive) matched the pencil bind-stub child def `oven_bind#1`, treating bind point as if it were an appliance and falsely passing. New v2 logic: bind points (oven_bind / m_oven_bind / fridge_bind) signal what appliance class is EXPECTED; validator searches scene-wide for matching def name (top-level instances + child counts) excluding bind-stubs themselves. This also handles Villu pattern where `SIEMENS HB23AB520E` sits as top-level instance, not as PD1_6 child.

**New validator (12 → 13):** `module_widths_min_350_max_600_with_symmetry` v1 — Studiokook distribution rule. Width band [350, 600] mm enforced on `:base_cabinet`, `:sink_base`, `:dishwasher`. Roles exempt: `cooktop_base` (width tracks Miele KM 6322 / BOSCH PIB / etc. cooktop appliance dimension), `l_corner_lower` (corner geometry ~900-1200mm), pencils (column ~600mm fixed), uppers (separate rule). Adaptive row-axis detection: module flush to N or S wall → width = bb[0] (X-extent); flush to W or E wall → width = bb[1] (Y-extent). Modules without any wall match → skipped (likely mis-classified). Symmetry analysis (residue distribution per row) deferred to v2 — needs row clustering by Y-position.

**Verification:** Villu Scene returns ok=true on all 13/13 validators. Module widths detected: BD1=600, BI=600, BD2#1=489, BD2#2=489 — all within band. Negative test: shrink BD1 to 200mm → fired with «width=200.0mm out of band [350, 600]». No orphans (`validators_without_rule=[]`, `rules_without_validator=[]`).

**Coverage now: 13/38 (34.2%).** Decision to keep Wave 5 to one new validator instead of three: `lower_corner_door_faces_adjacent_row` and `eurocut_mama_papa_assignment` need deeper analysis (sketch ground truth for door swing direction; full eurocut AD schema for mama/papa balance vs water-protection conflict resolution) — better as their own Wave 6 with proper scope.

