### EK validator coverage 9/38 → 12/38 (2026-05-04 Wave 4)

Three new validators on top of Wave 3 — all snapshot-derivable, no scene-meta required.

**Wave 4 (commit `16473fa`):**

1. **`pencil_appliances_required_when_host`** — oven_pencil/fridge_pencil instances must contain at least one appliance child def. Per-role regex: `(SIEMENS|BOSCH|Bosch|Samsung|Electrolux|Whirlpool|Miele|AEG|Gorenje|HB\d|HM\d|HBA|HMG|microwave|oven)` for ovens; `(холодильник|fridge|refrigerator|KGN|KGV|KIR|RB\d|fridge_integ)` for fridges. Snapshot extension: `child_def_counts` walk now also fires for `:oven_pencil` and `:fridge_pencil` roles, not only corners. Single-level walk depth.

2. **`upper_row_top_z_equals_ceiling_minus_30`** v1 — asymmetric topline check. Modal upper top Z is the row-line reference; only uppers ABOVE modal+5mm flagged (sticking up = bug). Below-modal uppers ALLOWED (intentional shorter modules — over hood, under-antresol variants, shelf-gap composition). Ceiling-30 heuristic for {2400, 2500, 2600, 2700, 2800} ±10mm — informational note when no match, no error (custom-ceiling kitchens like 2785 stay ok). v2 will read scene-meta `studiokook_meta:ceiling_mm` AD for absolute check. Why asymmetric: Villu has 9 uppers @ top=2755 + 1 @ top=2405 (TB1#3 short over hood) — symmetric consistency-check is too noisy on real kitchens.

3. **`appliance_semantics`** v1 — host-role↔appliance presence-pair. BD3 (cooktop_base) in scene → cooktop appliance def must exist (Miele KM* / BOSCH PIB* / Electrolux GK* / Teka EG*). oven_pencil → SIEMENS HB / BOSCH HB / etc. fridge_pencil → integrated fridge def. Spatial pairing (appliance directly over host) needs scene-meta — v1 catches «host present but no matching appliance anywhere» class of bugs.

**Verification:** clean Villu Scene.skp returns `ok=true` across all 12/12 validators, 0 orphans. 3 negative tests via snapshot mutation:
- inject empty `oven_pencil` with no appliance children → fired
- inject `upper_cabinet` at top_z=2855 (modal+100mm) → fired
- strip cooktop appliance defs from snapshot → fired

**Coverage now: 12/38 (31.6%).** Remaining easy targets: `panel_facade_section_canonical`, `panel_facade_via_def_instance`, `lower_corner_door_faces_adjacent_row` (def-name suffix L/R), `module_widths_min_350_max_600_with_symmetry`, `over_fridge_mezzanine_required`. Hard targets needing scene-meta: `upper_corner_orientation_matches_door_swing`, `wall_end_filler_applies_to_uppers_and_mezzanine`, `perpendicular_upper_row_uses_corner_bind_axis`, `wall_panel_orientation_in_wall_plane`.

**Files:**
- `easykitchen/scripts/ek_validators/{pencil_appliances_required_when_host,upper_row_top_z_equals_ceiling_minus_30,appliance_semantics}.rb`
- `easykitchen/scripts/ek_standards.rb` — `ModelSnapshot.instance_info` extends `child_def_counts` walk to pencils, 3 new `has_validator: true` flags
- Orphan check: 12 validators ↔ 12 has_validator rules, both lists empty

**Status:** code committed; live-tested on Villu Scene.skp — 12/12 validators ok=true canonical, 3 negative tests fired & passed.

