### Gemini CLI ripgrep optimization (2026-05-02)

**Context:** Gemini CLI online smoke test worked, but printed
`Ripgrep is not available. Falling back to GrepTool.`. That would make
repo/code-search tasks slower and less predictable.

**Decision:** Inspected Gemini CLI bundle and found it expects
`bundle/vendor/ripgrep/rg-win32-x64.exe`, but the installed npm package lacked
that file. Copied the existing Codex-vendored `rg.exe` into Gemini's expected
bundle path and added a `Gemini bundled ripgrep` check to
`C:/Users/sorte/.claude/hooks/maintenance/ai-cli-health.js`.

**Result:** Gemini can use its ripgrep path instead of falling back to GrepTool.
The optimization is health-checked, so future Gemini CLI upgrades that remove
the copied binary will be detected.

**Verification:** `gemini.cmd --version` returned `0.40.1`.
`gemini.cmd -p "Search this current directory for the word ARKHOS and return only: RG_OK" --include-directories C:/Users/sorte/.codex`
returned `RG_OK` without the ripgrep fallback warning. `node -c ai-cli-health.js`
passed and `node ai-cli-health.js` returned `[AI-CLI] OK 7/7`.

**Status:** Active; re-check after Gemini CLI upgrades.


### Codex fallback orchestrator layer (2026-05-02)

**Context:** The user asked whether Codex should get infrastructure to become a
full Claude analog when Claude Code hits limits. Full parallel infrastructure
would duplicate hooks, memory, lifecycle, and control-plane state, increasing
conflict risk.

**Decision:** Added a thin Codex fallback layer instead of a second control
plane. Created `C:/Users/sorte/.codex/ARKHOS-RUNBOOK.md`, extended
`.codex/AGENTS.md`, and reflected the fallback model in
`C:/Users/sorte/.claude/CLAUDE.md`, `system-state.md`, and
`agent-architecture.md`.

**Result:** Codex can operate ARKHOS manually when Claude Code is rate-limited:
run health/drift checks, patch shared files, operate project repos, update
vault/changelog, and hand work back to Claude. Codex must not create duplicate
Claude lifecycle hooks, duplicate memory systems, or claim Claude-native
behavior is verified without Claude restart/live check.

**Verification:** Rollback copies were written to
`C:/tmp/AGENTS.md.before-codex-fallback-20260502`,
`C:/tmp/CLAUDE.md.before-codex-fallback-20260502`,
`C:/tmp/system-state.md.before-codex-fallback-20260502`, and
`C:/tmp/agent-architecture.md.before-codex-fallback-20260502`. Repository HEAD
before edit was `07f123cafdbccb5fb24b4a6f09c235bf266ae7e9`. Files were patched
and re-read after write. Live Claude startup cache is not verified until Claude
Code restarts.

**Status:** Active.


### Gemini specialist contract alignment (2026-05-02)

**Context:** Codex was promoted to peer engineering agent, and Claude's control
plane was updated to role-based peer-agent routing. Gemini already had ARKHOS
subagents for mega-context, multimodal, and utility tasks, but its component
card still used old "second brain / Claude main orchestrator" language and did
not clearly state the read-only specialist boundary.

**Decision:** Added a Gemini Specialist Contract to
`C:/Users/sorte/.claude/CLAUDE.md` and updated
`10-Projects/ARKHOS/components/gemini-cli.md`, `system-state.md`, and
`agent-architecture.md`. Gemini remains a specialist
delegate for mega-context, multimodal, public web grounding, and cheap bulk
routine transforms. It is explicitly not a peer write-agent.

**Result:** ARKHOS now separates the three AI roles cleanly: Claude Code as
legacy control-plane runtime, Codex as peer engineer, Gemini as read-only
specialist delegate. Web grounding is public-data only; >20MB media/binary work
requires File API/fallback instead of pretending CLI support exists.

**Verification:** Rollback copies were written to
`C:/tmp/CLAUDE.md.before-gemini-contract-20260502` and
`C:/tmp/gemini-cli.md.before-gemini-contract-20260502`; repository HEAD before
edit was `07f123cafdbccb5fb24b4a6f09c235bf266ae7e9`. Files were patched and
re-read after write. Distillation pass also synchronized `system-state.md` and
`agent-architecture.md` so operational summaries match the Gemini specialist
boundary. Live Claude startup cache is not verified until Claude Code restarts.

**Status:** Active.


