orchestrator allowed to route findings to vault.

**Decision:** Added a `Peer-Agent Operating Model` section to
`C:/Users/sorte/.claude/CLAUDE.md` and updated the librarian ownership map. The
new contract keeps Claude Code as the legacy hook/runtime orchestrator, keeps
Gemini as a specialist delegate, and recognizes direct Codex sessions as peer
engineering sessions governed by `C:/Users/sorte/.codex/AGENTS.md`.

**Result:** Claude-side startup context and librarian routing now match the
peer-agent model: equal authority to reason and challenge, role-based write
zones, and evidence-first arbitration rather than model identity.

**Verification:** Rollback copies were written to `C:/tmp/CLAUDE.md.before-peer-roles-20260502`
