**Context:** User requested an n8n version update. Live VPS check showed `docker-compose.yml` uses unpinned `n8nio/n8n` and the running container reported n8n `2.18.5`, while older component docs still claimed `2.37.3`.

**Decision:** Created a pre-update rollback set under `/opt/n8n/backups/`: compose copy plus PostgreSQL custom-format dump `n8n-pre-upgrade-20260502-065546.dump` (250 MB). Ran `docker compose pull n8n` and `docker compose up -d n8n` to refresh the runtime image and recreate only the n8n container.

**Verification:** Before and after version both reported `2.18.5`; the pull completed and container was recreated at `2026-05-02T06:56:37Z`. Local `http://127.0.0.1:5678/healthz` returned `{"status":"ok"}` and external `https://n8n.studiokook.ee/healthz` returned HTTP 200. Startup logs show active workflows reactivated and editor available.

**Follow-up:** Startup logs warn that Python 3 is missing for internal Python task runner and that `/home/node/.n8n/binaryData` will be renamed to `/home/node/.n8n/storage` in n8n v3. PostgreSQL dump warned about a collation version mismatch; track separately before DB maintenance.

**Status:** Refreshed and verified; no version bump because upstream image matched running version.


