### Windows Scheduled Tasks audit cleanup

**Context:** Scheduled Task count had grown and some jobs predated the scheduled-first refresh/health work.

**Decision:** Audited user/ARKHOS tasks. Disabled, but did not delete, two obsolete/broken tasks: `\QMD Vault Reindex` (superseded by `\ARKHOS\QMD Refresh`) and `\ARKHOS\Vault Audit` (target `vault-audit-hidden.vbs` no longer exists; `vault-audit.js` remains a SessionStart hook).

**Verification:** `\ARKHOS\Health Check`, `\ARKHOS\Drift Check`, and `\ARKHOS\QMD Refresh` were manually run through Task Scheduler and returned Last Result `0`. `\ARKHOS-AutoLibrarian` still runs, but its internal log shows recent `claude -p failed` on distill attempts, so it remains on the watchlist rather than being disabled.

**Status:** Active cleanup. Next target: repair or redesign AutoLibrarian distill execution.

### QMD scheduled-first refresh

**Context:** QMD search was repaired, but freshness still depended on remembering to run `qmd update` and `qmd embed`. That violates the ARKHOS operating rule that maintenance should be autonomous.

**Decision:** Added `C:/Users/sorte/.claude/hooks/maintenance/qmd-refresh.js` with a lock file, state file, and log. Registered Windows Scheduled Task `\ARKHOS\QMD Refresh` every 6 hours via hidden VBS wrapper. The task runs `qmd update`, runs `qmd embed` when needed, and records compact state.

**Verification:** Manual run returned `[QMD] OK embed=true`; state file shows successful update/embed. Scheduled task is Ready and battery-tolerant. Health-check now includes both QMD index freshness and QMD refresh task/state.

**Status:** Active.

### QMD search repair and freshness check

**Context:** QMD status showed live SQLite collections, but `qmd search "..." -c vault` failed with `Collection not found: vault` because the YAML config `C:/Users/sorte/.config/qmd/index.yml` was missing from the operational path. The hook QMD constant also pointed to an old Bun install whose `store.js` lacked the Windows `USERPROFILE` fallback.

**Decision:** Restored `index.yml` from the live SQLite collections (`vault`, `ghost-.claude`, `trading-knowledge`). Switched `hooks/shared/paths.js` to the npm QMD CLI JS path and changed active QMD callers to invoke `node qmd.js` directly instead of going through Bash. This avoids WSL `/c/...` path failures and PowerShell shim problems.

**Verification:** Ran `qmd update`: `vault` indexed 265 new and 61 updated docs; total index is now 1101 docs (`vault` 531, `ghost-.claude` 376, `trading-knowledge` 194). Ran `qmd embed`: 176 docs / 1348 chunks embedded. `qmd search "n8n report digest" -c vault` now returns `observations/n8n-report-digest-20260430.md` as top result. Auto-search worker wrote fresh QMD results to `.autosearch-cache.md`.

**Status:** Verified. Health-check now includes QMD collection/config/vector freshness.

### AI CLI delegation hardening

**Context:** Codex CLI and Gemini CLI are now part of ARKHOS delegation, but the operational state needed a current version check, Windows shim guidance, and a no-quota health path.

**Decision:** Updated local Gemini CLI from `0.40.0` to `0.40.1`; Codex CLI remains current at `0.128.0`. Added `C:/Users/sorte/.claude/hooks/maintenance/ai-cli-health.js` and wired it into `health-check.js` so scheduled health verifies package versions, `.cmd` shims, component docs, and delegation agents without spending model quota.

**Gotcha:** On Windows PowerShell, direct `gemini`/`codex` can resolve to `.ps1` shims and fail under ExecutionPolicy. Operational docs now prefer `C:/Users/sorte/AppData/Roaming/npm/gemini.cmd` and `codex.cmd`.

**Status:** Active. Remaining improvements: `delegate-second-brain` router, Gemini File API fallback for >20MB media, optional Codex review hook for critical diffs.

### n8n report delivery digest

**Context:** Scheduled n8n workflows could spam Telegram with separate regular reports: SEO/AEO/Analytics/Data Retention, trading daily/weekly reports, COT, seasonality. Realtime alerts are still useful, but scheduled report delivery should be consolidated.

**Decision:** Added local digest script `C:/Users/sorte/.claude/hooks/maintenance/n8n-report-digest.js` and Windows task `\ARKHOS\n8n Report Digest` at 10:00 daily. Muted only regular Telegram report nodes in 10 workflows; realtime alert nodes remain enabled. Backups: `C:/tmp/n8n-muted-report-nodes-20260430/*.json`.

**Verification:** `n8n-report-digest.js --force` sent one digest. `C:/tmp/n8n-assert-muted-report-nodes.js` confirmed 10 regular report nodes disabled and 11 realtime alert nodes still enabled. Task power settings set to battery-tolerant.

**Status:** Active. Observation: [[observations/n8n-report-digest-20260430]].

